children.subject: I have checked with my advisor and she said that community college courses satisfy those requirements.
Then I think you should be good, but apparently I don’t have the final say as a student.
My advisor said it is good, but I would like to hear some opinions from others students.

looks good to me, make sure you have enough cc classes transferred to meet both natural science elective and technical elective requirements. See degree worksheet here: https://engineering.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/eecs-worksheet-2020.pdf

history.content: I am majoring in EECS. I have transferred from my community college and have met all of the 4 lower division H/SS requirements, and took all of the required math, science, and English courses. I took the equivalent course for CS 61A. In fall 2020, my first semester at Berkeley, I have taken EECS 16A, CS 61B, and Music 139 (upper div. H/SS). In spring 2021, I took EECS 16B and CS 70. In fall 2021, I will take CS 61C, CS 195 (ethics), and EE 120. In spring 2022, I will take Music 137AC (An email says that there is a fairly good chance it will be offered this semester. This course meets both American Cultures and upper div. H/SS requirements), EE 105, and EE 130 (design). In fall 2022 (my last semester at Berkeley), I plan to take CS 160 and EECS 151+LB (design). Do all of my classes satisfy my degree worksheet? Is this a good schedule plan?
history.subject: Remaining Class schedule at Berkeley
